    <text><body>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <pb n="27r" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000055.jpg"/>
                    <hi rendition="#uu"><placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0006863 https://www.geonames.org/1252558">Himalaya.</placeName></hi><note place="right" hand="#author"><ref xml:id="ed_ytm_3mg_hy" type="siglum" target="#Geographie_der_Pflanzen_D">D.</ref></note></p>
                <p>Observations <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">de</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">sur</add>
                    </subst> la géographie des plantes <lb/>par le <persName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0013583 https://d-nb.info/gnd/1282994832">Docteur
                            <hi rendition="#uu">George Govan</hi></persName> (entre les
                    <lb/>rivières <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0016350 https://www.geonames.org/1252798">Jumna</placeName> et <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">Sutledge</del>
                        <add place="intralinear"><placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0018184 https://www.geonames.org/1115006">Sutledge</placeName></add>
                    </subst>.)<supplied cert="high">.</supplied><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/VWSWNKTG">
                        <lb/><choice>
                            <abbr><hi rendition="#u">Edinb.</hi></abbr>
                            <expan><hi rendition="#u">Edinburgh</hi></expan>
                        </choice><hi rendition="#u"> </hi><choice>
                            <abbr><hi rendition="#u">Journ.</hi></abbr>
                            <expan><hi rendition="#u">Journal</hi></expan>
                        </choice><hi rendition="#u"> of Science </hi><choice>
                            <abbr><hi rendition="#u">Jan.</hi></abbr>
                            <expan><hi rendition="#u">January</hi></expan>
                        </choice><hi rendition="#u"> 1825. </hi><choice>
                            <abbr><hi rendition="#u">p.</hi></abbr>
                            <expan><hi rendition="#u">page</hi></expan>
                        </choice><hi rendition="#u"> 17.</hi></bibl>
                </p>
                <note place="right" hand="#author" rend="sticked"><pb n="26r" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000053.jpg"/>Le cryptogame que l’on croit <supplied cert="high">être</supplied>
                    <lb/>la cause de la neige rouge <lb/>a été découvert récemment <lb/>aussi en
                        <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0010177 https://www.geonames.org/2661886">Suède</placeName>
                    <lb/>par <persName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0012515 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118643959">Agardh</persName><supplied cert="high">.</supplied><pb n="26v" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000054.jpg"/>
                    <gap unit="pages" quantity="1" reason="empty"/></note>
                <p>Les <choice>
                        <sic>pleines</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">plaines</corr>
                </choice> de la partie Nord<supplied cert="high">-</supplied>ouest de <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0006867 https://www.geonames.org/1114958">l’Indostan</placeName>
                    <lb/>ne <choice>
                        <sic>s’ébuent</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">s’ébouent</corr>
                    </choice> jusqu’à <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0009719 https://www.geonames.org/1257806">Saharanpore</placeName> encore
                    <lb/>que de <measure quantity="800" unit="foot">800</measure> ou <measure quantity="1000" unit="foot">1000 pieds anglais</measure>.</p>
                <p>Les parties humides sont couvertes d’espèces <lb/>gigantesques de <name type="plant">Saccharum</name><supplied cert="high">,</supplied> dans
                    lesquelles <lb/>les éléphans se tiennent pendant la <lb/>saison des
                        pluies<supplied cert="high">,</supplied> surtout autour de <lb/><placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0008017 https://www.geonames.org/1257806">Padshahmuhul</placeName>, jadis séjour <choice>
                        <sic>favorit</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">favori</corr>
                    </choice>
                    <lb/>des Empereurs de <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0005507 https://www.geonames.org/1273294">Delhi</placeName>.</p>
                <p>Les <choice>
                        <sic>pleines</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">plaines</corr>
                    </choice> plus sèches (toujours au<supplied cert="high">-</supplied>dessous
                    <lb/>de <measure quantity="1000" unit="foot">1000 pieds</measure>) ont une
                    physionomie <lb/>africaine. En <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0002331 https://www.geonames.org/6255146">Afrique</placeName><supplied cert="high">,</supplied> c’est l’<name type="plant">Asclepias <lb/>gigantea</name> et <name type="plant">Rhamnus
                        Lotus</name>, ici<supplied cert="high">,</supplied> c’est <lb/>l’<name type="plant">Asclepias syriaca</name> et <name type="plant">Ziziphus
                        <lb/>jujuba</name>, qui <choice>
                        <sic>caractérise</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">caractérisent</corr>
                    </choice> la végétation. <lb/>Les petites collines sont couvertes <lb/>de <name type="plant">Barberia <subst>
                            <del rendition="#s">B</del>
                            <add place="intralinear">prionitis</add>
                        </subst></name> et <name type="plant">Capparis <lb/><choice>
                            <sic>heteroclyta</sic>
                            <corr cert="high">heteroclita</corr>
                        </choice></name>, <name type="plant">Salvadora persica</name>
                    <add place="superlinear">et</add> plusieurs <lb/><pb n="27v" facs="http://content.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/dms/PPN838243592/1200/0/00000056.jpg"/>Mimoses, <name type="plant" key="Mimosa seerisa"><choice>
                            <abbr>M.</abbr>
                            <expan>Mimosa</expan>
                        </choice> Seerissa</name>, <name type="plant" key="Mimosa arabica">arabica</name>, <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">et</del>
                        <lb/>
                        <add place="intralinear"><name type="plant" key="Mimosa farnesiaca"><choice>
                                    <sic>farnesiana</sic>
                                    <corr cert="high">farnesiaca</corr>
                                </choice></name></add>
                    </subst> et <name type="plant" key="Mimosa catechu">Catechu</name>, de <name type="plant"><choice>
                            <sic>Boutea</sic>
                            <corr cert="high">Butea</corr>
                        </choice>
                        <lb/>frondosa</name>, et surtout de <name type="plant"><choice>
                            <sic>Capparis</sic>
                            <corr cert="high">Caparis</corr>
                        </choice> aphylla</name>, <lb/>et le superbe <name type="plant">Pergularia
                        odoratissima</name>. <lb/>Le <name type="plant">Pinus longifolia</name> de
                        <persName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0001103 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117598275"><choice>
                            <abbr>Roxb.</abbr>
                            <expan>Roxburgh</expan>
                        </choice></persName> est encore <lb/>très rare.</p>
                <p>En s’élevant de <measure quantity="1000" unit="foot">1000</measure> à <measure quantity="3000" unit="foot">3000 pieds</measure><supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/>on commence à trouver <add place="superlinear">des forêts</add> de <name type="plant">Shorea <lb/>robusta</name>, de <name type="plant">Dalbergia
                        Sissoo</name>, de <lb/><name type="plant">Murraya exotica</name>, de <name type="plant">Gmelina arborea</name>, <lb/>sur lesquelles <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">rappen rap</del>
                        <add place="intralinear"><choice>
                                <sic>rempent</sic>
                                <corr>rampent</corr>
                            </choice></add>
                    </subst>
                    <lb/>le <name type="plant">Hastingia coccinea</name>, des <name type="plant" key="Echiteae">Echites</name> et <lb/>des <name type="plant">Smilax</name>.
                        Au<supplied cert="high">-</supplied>dessus de <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">350</del>
                        <add place="intralinear"><measure quantity="3500" unit="foot">3500</measure></add>
                    </subst><measure quantity="3500" unit="foot"> pieds</measure><supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/><choice>
                        <abbr>p.</abbr>
                        <expan>par</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <abbr>e.</abbr>
                        <expan>exemple</expan>
                    </choice> près de la ville de <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0001539 https://www.geonames.org/1262151">Nahn</placeName><supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <lb/>le <name type="plant">Pinus longifolia</name>, <add place="left"><metamark/>que les indigènes <lb/>appellent <lb/><name type="plant" subtype="vernacular" key="Pinus longifolia">Cheer</name>, et <lb/>deux
                        espèces de <name type="plant" subtype="vernacular" key="Quercus">Chênes</name><note place="mBottom" hand="#author">2 species welche die
                            Eingebohrenen nen̅en
                            <hi rendition="#u">Ban</hi> und <hi rendition="#u">Mohroo</hi>.</note></add>
                    <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">prend son</del>
                        <add place="intralinear">prennent leur</add>
                    </subst>
                    <lb/>plus grand <choice>
                        <sic>dévelloppement</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">développement</corr>
                    </choice>. <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s"><gap unit="words" quantity="1" reason="illegible"/></del>
                        <add place="intralinear">
                            <lb/>C’est</add>
                    </subst> là que <choice>
                        <sic>végète</sic>
                        <corr cert="high">végètent</corr>
                    </choice>
                    <name type="plant">Andromeda <lb/>ovalifolia</name>
                    <persName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0006224 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117126314"><choice>
                            <abbr>Wall.</abbr>
                            <expan>Wallich</expan>
                        </choice></persName><supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                    <name type="plant">Morus serrata</name>, <name type="plant">Rho<g ref="#typoHyphen"/><lb break="no"/>dodendron puniceum</name>, <name type="plant">Rubia <choice>
                            <sic>munjet</sic>
                            <corr cert="high">munjeet</corr>
                        </choice></name>, <lb/>des <name type="plant">Berberis</name> et des <name type="plant">Crataegus</name> à <lb/>forme entièrement <placeName ref="https://editon-humboldt.de/H0005696 https://www.geonames.org/6255148">européenne</placeName>. Le <lb/><name type="plant">Pinus
                        deodara</name> ne se montre que sur des <lb/><del rendition="#s">plus
                        hauts</del> sommets de <measure quantity="7000" unit="foot">7000</measure> à
                        <measure quantity="8000" unit="foot">8000 pieds</measure>. </p>
                <p><add place="left"><choice>
                            <orig>dans</orig>
                            <reg>Dans</reg>
                        </choice> les ravins<supplied cert="high">,</supplied> on trouve <lb/>encore
                            <name type="plant">Habenaria gi<g ref="#typoHyphen"/><lb break="no"/>gantea</name> et <name type="plant" key="Habenaria pectinata">pectinata</name>.</add>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body></text>
